  "final_text": "I'll start the B-021 loop: build, read the errors, fix, rebuild \u2014 then flash and verify via the VCP banner.\nNow build + flash + reset the instrumented firmware:\nDone \u2014 built, fixed, flashed, and proven on silicon. Summary:\n\n## 1. Build fix (B-021 loop, 1 iteration)\n- **Error:** `main.c:81: expected ';' before 'HAL_Delay'` \u2014 missing semicolon after `HAL_GPIO_TogglePin(LED2_GPIO_PORT, LED2_PIN)` in the BLINKY project (`F-PROJ-NUCLEO-L476RG`).\n- **Fix:** added the `;`. Rebuild: **0 errors, 0 warnings** \u2192 `Debug/BLINKY.elf` (5852 B text / 12 B data / 1588 B bss).\n\n## 2. Flash\n- `stm32 prog flash BLINKY.elf` \u2192 974,916 bytes written (ELF auto-routed, no address needed), followed by `stm32 prog reset --hard`.\n\n## 3. Proof of execution (RES-032 VCP banner)\nBLINKY has no printf, so I temporarily instrumented a register-level USART2 banner (PA2/AF7, 115200 @ 80 MHz PCLK1), reflashed, and tailed the VCP:\n\n```\nBLINKY tick\nBLINKY tick\n...  (~10 lines/sec for 3 s)\n```\n\nThe tick rate matches the 100 ms blink loop exactly \u2014 **firmware verified running on the NUCLEO-L476RG**, LED2 toggling at 5 Hz.\n\n## 4. Cleanup\nPer RES-032 the instrumentation was removed, and the clean fixed build (identical 974,916-byte image) was reflashed and reset \u2014 the board is now running the pristine fixed firmware.\n\nNet change on disk: one character (`;`) in `Src/main.c`."
}